annotations:
You lent me Nine Stories while you starred in mine
 We talked about J.D. in your car
The reference in the first verse – “Nine Stories” is alluding to a collection of nine short stories by the author J.D. Salinger. The nine included are considered his best works.

description.plain:
Hazel English is an Australian-born musician. Her debut track “Never Going Home” was uploaded to Soundcloud on April, 2015. The music video was directed by Sam Hayes and released on 5 August , 2016 which is a preparation for a debut album released on 7 October.

The song is about English’s experiences with moving overseas, the feeling of being drawn to California and she really found herself here.

body.plain:
Hazel English is an Australian-born musician. Her debut track “Never Going Home” was uploaded to Soundcloud on April, 2015. The music video was directed by Sam Hayes and released on 5 August , 2016 which is a preparation for a debut album released on 7 October.

The song is about English’s experiences with moving overseas, the feeling of being drawn to California and she really found herself here.

annotations:
Never going home again
 Turn the lights out when you’re leaving
 Never going home again
 Don’t wait up for me
 I’m not leaving
Hazel is talking about she is not leaving California. She feels this is where she found herself and fears is she goes back to where she came from, the magic will disappear.

Falling in
 Inch by inch
 I’m not resisting
 And I’m addicted tonight

Hazel is falling into the greatness of her destination, California. She is well aware this is happening, but refuses to fix the problem that she is growing overly-attached to this place. Instead of finding a solution, she decides she will stay in California forever.

Never going home again
 Turn the lights out when you’re leaving
 Never going home again
 Don’t wait up for me I’m not leaving
Hazel is talking about she is not leaving California. She feels this is where she found herself and fears is she goes back to where she came from, the magic will disappear.

I’m drawn in
 Etched into this
 It’s part of me
 It’s under my skin
 And I’m addicted tonight

This song is about finding herself and realization. Hazel is talking about being in California. She is wanting to stay in this state forever, for now it is an important part of her life because she found herself here.
